goals.question: Which aircraft make and model has the highest number of bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This helps identify aircrafts that are more prone to bird strikes and can inform decisions on aircraft design and maintenance.

goals.rationale: This helps understand the severity of bird strikes and can inform decisions on aircraft safety measures.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Airport_Name').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Airport_Name', y='count', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    aircraft_counts = data.groupby('Aircraft_Make_Model')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    aircraft_counts = aircraft_counts.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Aircraft_Make_Model', y='count', data=aircraft_counts)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('Which aircraft make and model has the highest number of bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Effect_Amount_of_damage', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of damage caused by bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Aircraft_Airline_Operator'] = data['Aircraft_Airline_Operator'].astype('category')
    data = data.groupby('Aircraft_Airline_Operator').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Aircraft_Airline_Operator', y='counts', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.axhline(y=data['counts'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['counts'].max()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which airline operator has the highest number of bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
